loop UXScoreRepair(flow):
  goal: user flow reaches defined completion and quality threshold
  context:
    URL, user task, supported screen sizes, modes, rubric, product constraints, and regression checks
  authority:
    may edit UI code, copy, spacing, layout, and non-contract visual behavior
    may not change authentication, billing, data model, public API, security policy, or analytics semantics without approval
  cycle:
    observe:
      start from fresh browser state
      complete the flow
      capture screens
      score each screen with the same checklist
    act:
      improve the weakest safe area with one bounded change
    verify:
      rerun the full flow
      rescore screens with the same checklist
      run regression checks
    decide:
      keep if: score improves and no regression appears
      revert if: score drops, completion breaks, or behavior changes outside authority
      escalate if: product, security, access, or data decision is needed
  stop:
    success if: completion criterion and quality threshold are met
    no_op if: flow already meets the threshold
    stall if: two full passes show no score gain
    budget if: time, token, or iteration budget is reached
    blocked if: access, environment, test data, or approval is unavailable
  return:
    scores, screenshots, changed files, checks run, stop reason, and next action

